# ai-control-plane .cursorrules — 6-layer governance
# Priority: L0 > L1 > L2 > L3 > L4 > L5
# Conflict resolution: higher layer always wins
# Detail: docs/governance/CURSOR_RISK_POLICY.md
# Last updated: 2026-06-22 (Milestones A/B/C/C+ CLOSED; Public Beta IN PROGRESS)

## L0 — Behavioral Constitution (Karpathy 4 Principles)
# These apply to EVERY task, no exceptions

THINK BEFORE CODING:
- Before any code: state explicitly (a) files you will touch, (b) assumptions being made, (c) verify command
- If uncertain about interpretation → ask, do NOT pick silently and run with it
- If a simpler approach exists → say so before implementing the complex one
- "Senior engineer test": would a senior say this is overcomplicated? If yes, simplify first.

SIMPLICITY FIRST:
- Minimum code that solves the problem. Nothing speculative.
- No abstractions for single-use code; no "flexibility" not requested
- If 100 lines could be 50 → propose the rewrite, don't add to 100
- No error handling for impossible scenarios

SURGICAL CHANGES:
- Touch ONLY what the task requires. Every changed line must trace to the request.
- Do NOT "improve" adjacent code, comments, or formatting unless asked
- If you notice dead code → mention it, do NOT delete it
- Remove only imports/variables YOUR changes made unused (not pre-existing)

GOAL-DRIVEN EXECUTION:
- Every task must have explicit verify: [command] — state it before starting
- Transform "fix the bug" → "write test reproducing it, then make it pass"
- Multi-step tasks: state plan with verify per step before executing step 1

## L1 — Project Context

Package: ai_control_plane (src/ layout). CLI: agentctl (Typer). API: FastAPI api/server.py.
Config: Pydantic v2 + PyYAML via ACP_CONFIG_DIR env var.
Read ARCHITECTURE.md before any non-trivial task. It is the L1 authority.

Module ownership (who must review changes):
- core/policies.py → Claude architecture review required (CRITICAL)
- core/models.py → Claude review required (HIGH)
- config/loader.py → Claude review required (HIGH)
- api/server.py → Cursor-OK with invariant check (MEDIUM)
- apex/ → Claude design spec required before implement (HIGH)
- mcp/ → Cursor-OK with invariant #3 check (MEDIUM)
- tests/, docs/ → Cursor-OK (LOW)

Coding conventions:
- Pydantic v2 (ConfigDict, not class Config)
- structlog everywhere (not logging stdlib)
- Async/await for all I/O. Type hints on all public signatures.
- Docstring 1 line per public class/function
- Classes: PascalCase; functions/vars: snake_case; constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
- Config env vars: ACP_ prefix (ACP_CONFIG_DIR, ACP_API_URL, ACP_DATA_DIR, ACP_REDIS_URL)

Error handling:
- Domain errors: ControlPlaneError hierarchy (core/exceptions.py)
- HTTP: HTTPException with status_code + detail JSON
- MCP: McpError(code, message, data) — no raw exceptions
- Log before raise: logger.error("...", exc_info=True)

Test requirements:
- Each core/ module has tests/test_{module}.py; use conftest.py fixtures
- Integration tests: real PolicyEngine with fixture YAML — do not mock PolicyEngine

Milestone status (do not contradict ARCHITECTURE.md):
- Milestones A, B, C, C+ — CLOSED. apex/ SAPAL loop is live.
- Public Beta — IN PROGRESS (soak + flip). See docs/governance/PUBLIC_BETA_SPRINT_PLAN.md

## L2 — Risk Policy

Full policy: docs/governance/CURSOR_RISK_POLICY.md

Task risk levels — MUST classify before starting:
LOW:    docs-only, test additions, comment fixes → proceed, max 50 LOC changed
MEDIUM: new tests, CLI additions, config changes → state plan first, max 200 LOC
HIGH:   core/ changes, API schema changes, new endpoints → Claude review mid-task, max 300 LOC
CRITICAL: PolicyEngine, ABAC, invariant-touching, identity auth → human explicit approve first

Forbidden operations (absolute — no exceptions):
1. Direct push or merge to master without explicit human instruction
2. Remove, rename, or weaken any of the 8 invariants (ARCHITECTURE.md)
3. Import OSS policy engines (CrewAI, LangChain, AutoGen, etc.) into core/
4. Combine tasks of different risk levels in 1 PR
5. Commit without running the verify gate first
6. Closes #52..#62 range syntax — use individual Closes #N per issue

PR size limits:
LOW: max 50 LOC. MEDIUM: max 200 LOC. HIGH/CRITICAL: max 300 LOC.
If task exceeds limit → split into multiple PRs; do not waive without human approval.

## L3 — Execution Guardrails

Branch isolation:
Every task = new branch from master. Name: {risk-level}/{issue-id}-{short-desc}
Never reuse a branch for a different task scope.

File allowlists per task type:
docs-only:  allowed = *.md, docs/**, CHANGELOG.md | forbidden = src/**, tests/**
test-only:  allowed = tests/**, tests/fixtures/** | forbidden = src/** (if needed → MEDIUM)
core/:      allowed = src/ai_control_plane/core/**, tests/test_{module}.py
             forbidden = api/**, mcp/**, cli/** unless explicitly in task scope

Invariants (check before every src/ PR):
1. core/policies.py: no OSS policy engine imports
2. core/models.py: all new types here only, in __all__
3. mcp/git_server.py: facade only, no git logic in Python
4. cli/: no direct core/policies.py import — HTTP/API only
5. apex/: OSS tool calls FROM apex/, not the reverse
6. api/: sole cross-language bridge
7. core/quota.py: QuotaStore ABC, no hardcoded Redis
8. config/: ACP_CONFIG_DIR env var, no hardcoded paths

Additional NEVER rules:
- Default-allow on policy evaluation failure (always fail-closed)
- Hardcode Redis connection strings (env var or constructor injection)
- Git logic in Python (cyanheads TypeScript fork only)

## L4 — Evaluation

Mandatory verify gate (run in this order):
ruff check src/ tests/
mypy src/ai_control_plane/ --strict
pytest tests/ -v
pytest tests/test_smoke.py -v -m smoke
pytest tests/test_shipped_config_parity.py -v -m shipped_config

Coverage: fail_under = 70 (pyproject.toml). core/policies.py >= 80%. cli/ >= 60%.

Before declaring done:
- All verify gate commands pass
- No new mypy errors introduced
- PR diff reviewed for orthogonal changes (Surgical Changes check)
- GitHub issues linked individually in PR body (Closes #N, not ranges)

## L5 — Governance & Memory

Decision log: docs/governance/*.html — Claude architect decisions archived.
Change rationale: docs/governance/PHASE*_REPORT.md, MILESTONE_*_SPRINT_PLAN.md.
Failure patterns: docs/governance/LESSONS_LEARNED.md — update after each sprint.
Karpathy rearchitecture plan: docs/governance/ACP_KARPATHY_REARCHITECTURE_PLAN.md.
Cursor prompt template: docs/prompts/_TEMPLATE.md.

Lessons → rules loop: every failure pattern in LESSONS_LEARNED must map to an L0–L3 rule.

Sprint close checklist:
1. All GitHub issues closed with individual Closes #N
2. Doc drift fixed (ARCHITECTURE.md, sprint plans)
3. LESSONS_LEARNED.md updated with new patterns
4. .cursorrules reviewed for rule additions from lessons
